Global Plant Extract Drug Market Insights
Plant Extract Drug Market size was valued at USD 57 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 85 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 5.4% from 2024 to 2030.

Plant Extract Drug Market Overview
The global plant extract drug market is expected to experience significant growth in the coming years, driven by increasing consumer demand for natural remedies and alternative medicine. The market size is projected to reach USD 55.6 billion by 2027, growing at a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 8.2% from 2023 to 2027. The rising popularity of plant-based medicines, particularly in the treatment of chronic diseases, is one of the key factors fueling this growth. Moreover, increasing awareness about the side effects of synthetic drugs is pushing healthcare consumers toward plant extracts, as they are perceived to be safer and more sustainable. The market is also benefiting from advancements in extraction technologies, which have improved the efficacy and potency of plant-based drugs, making them more appealing to both healthcare providers and patients.

